00:28:13.900 --> 00:28:20.410
I can’t believe it. Everyone says
these roses are hard to take care of,

00:28:21.050 --> 00:28:23.050
but they’ve survived until now.

00:28:27.480 --> 00:28:29.960
Nothing is too hard if you try.

00:28:31.960 --> 00:28:35.220
You sound like a life coach.

00:28:36.560 --> 00:28:39.700
What’s a life coach?

00:28:40.800 --> 00:28:46.900
Someone who gives advice about life.

00:28:51.440 --> 00:28:55.540
Does that mean I’m a life coach
for these roses?

00:28:57.540 --> 00:28:58.820
No, Mr. Ramil.

00:28:58.850 --> 00:28:59.520
Oh?

00:29:00.120 --> 00:29:03.060
A life coach advises humans.

00:29:06.340 --> 00:29:09.220
What if I want a word to use with the roses?

00:29:17.840 --> 00:29:19.140
How about “Daddy”?

00:29:22.830 --> 00:29:24.340
You can be the daddy of these roses.

00:29:27.970 --> 00:29:30.620
Humans love using weird words, huh?

00:29:36.580 --> 00:29:37.880
Your Mommy’s giving you a shower.

00:29:37.900 --> 00:29:39.100
How are you feeling, babies?

00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:41.630
What are you talking about?

00:29:42.380 --> 00:29:46.110
Well, didn’t you say I’m their Daddy?

00:29:47.740 --> 00:29:49.540
Mommy, spray more water on our babies.

00:29:49.970 --> 00:29:51.180
They need it.

00:29:51.580 --> 00:29:55.080
Not Mommy. I’m their Papa.

00:29:56.160 --> 00:29:57.480
Alright, Papa.

00:29:58.320 --> 00:29:59.480
You do the spraying.

00:30:00.390 --> 00:30:01.790
Got it, Papa.

00:30:07.020 --> 00:30:07.890
Spray here too.

00:30:14.850 --> 00:30:18.330
Don’t forget to water them
and avoid harsh sunlight.

00:30:18.540 --> 00:30:21.820
I’ve already separated the ones that need
extra fertilizer,

00:30:22.070 --> 00:30:23.220
so remember to add it.

00:30:24.940 --> 00:30:26.240
Got it, Master.

00:30:28.790 --> 00:30:30.230
What are you guys talking about?

00:30:32.740 --> 00:30:34.180
Pong, we’ve talked about this.

00:30:34.550 --> 00:30:35.750
Why are you being fussy now?

00:30:36.240 --> 00:30:37.660
Come on, Punn.

00:30:38.080 --> 00:30:39.610
How am I supposed to feel?

00:30:39.640 --> 00:30:41.610
Happy that you’re moving away?

00:30:41.930 --> 00:30:43.930
If it were somewhere I could follow you,
I wouldn’t be complaining.

00:30:45.380 --> 00:30:47.120
Come here.

00:30:48.980 --> 00:30:49.880
Come on.

00:30:50.660 --> 00:30:52.320
Don’t forget me.

00:30:53.260 --> 00:30:57.190
How could I forget you? You’re my brother.

00:31:03.790 --> 00:31:10.190
By the way, Punn, will you really not age
if you stay there?

00:31:10.220 --> 00:31:11.620
Will you be this young forever?

00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:14.660
Yes. There’s no time there.

00:31:15.050 --> 00:31:17.050
Everything pauses in the present.

00:31:19.140 --> 00:31:23.140
I’m happy anywhere you’re happy.

00:31:27.140 --> 00:31:28.540
I’ll come visit, brother.

00:31:29.100 --> 00:31:29.880
Okay.

00:31:56.290 --> 00:31:57.920
Are you sure about this, Punn?

00:31:59.520 --> 00:32:00.550
Yes, I am.

00:32:01.320 --> 00:32:04.520
Like I said, I want to be with you forever.

00:32:15.500 --> 00:32:16.780
Then come live with me.

00:32:17.800 --> 00:32:19.180
Forever.

00:32:22.900 --> 00:32:24.300
♪ For even if ♪

00:32:24.310 --> 00:32:27.820
♪ The clock hands keep on turning ♪

00:32:27.850 --> 00:32:31.370
♪ I vow my love for you will keep on burning ♪

00:32:31.400 --> 00:32:34.940
♪ You’ll still have me when the night feels lonely ♪

00:32:34.960 --> 00:32:38.720
♪ You’ll still have me 'cause you belong with me ♪

00:32:45.700 --> 00:32:49.200
♪ And even if the stars and moonlight fade from view ♪

00:32:49.230 --> 00:32:54.220
♪ I vow our love will never lose its hue ♪

00:32:54.250 --> 00:32:56.300
♪ From my heart ♪

00:32:56.330 --> 00:33:00.710
♪ We’ll have each other, every day and forever ♪

00:33:16.100 --> 00:33:19.950
I can’t believe forever is real.

00:33:21.620 --> 00:33:23.740
Do I get to live here forever?

00:33:25.030 --> 00:33:27.030
Is there anything longer than forever?

00:33:28.430 --> 00:33:31.660
If you want it, I’ll give it to you.

00:33:33.390 --> 00:33:35.590
In your hundred-plus years of living,

00:33:36.590 --> 00:33:40.810
am I the first to get forever from you?

00:33:43.180 --> 00:33:48.580
You’re the only one
who gets forever from me.

00:34:10.679 --> 00:34:13.010
Do you know what this necklace means?

00:34:15.920 --> 00:34:18.090
I just know it’s as important as life.

00:34:34.889 --> 00:34:37.070
Nothing matters more than you, Punn.

00:34:44.489 --> 00:34:45.960
I love you.

00:34:49.960 --> 00:34:53.389
I love you too, Mr. Ramil.

00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:22.180
I’ve received it. Thank you.

00:35:22.540 --> 00:35:26.530
(Well, the owner of the painting…)

00:35:26.560 --> 00:35:27.940
It’s a beautiful painting.

00:35:37.580 --> 00:35:40.170
Nice to meet you, Mr. Methus.